Administration & Finance Assistant
Responsibilities
Currently one of our clients, a Dredging and Reclamation works, are looking for Administration and Finance Assistant, with job description:Managing accomodation of expatriate staff and visitors (Housing, Hotel0Arranging transport for staff and visitorsPersonnel and payroll administrationDealing with social insurance issues, tax-technial issues, legal regulations and required visaManaging visa applications for expatriate staff/ crewCompliance with all local and international tax obligationsMonthly declaration of taxes (Withholding tax, VAT, income taxes)Custom formalities and procedures for the importation of goods  Qualifications:Age with more than 25 years oldCandidate must possess at least a Diploma, Finance/Accountancy/Banking or equivalent.At least 2 year(s) of working experience in the related field is required for this position.has strong skills and proven experience of administrative workBeing well grounded in administrative mattersAdvanced knowledge of tax obligations and monthly tax declarationSpeaking fluently Indonesian and EnglishFluent knowledge of M. Office (Word, Excel, outlook)Applicants must be willing to work in Pantai Indah KapukWe treat our candidate resumes in a professional manner and strictly confidential, as our code of ethics.  If you meet the above requirements and interested with the position, please send your Curriculum Vitae in MS Word format with your photograph, to: hermaniar@jac-bc.co.id
